      "name": "Cause and Effect Worksheets"
    }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Free Cause and Effect Worksheets - Reading Comprehension | ToolCalcs"
  description={ws.description}
  type="article"
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <nav class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a> &rsaquo;
    <a href="/worksheets/">Worksheets</a> &rsaquo;
    <span>Cause and Effect Worksheets</span>
  </nav>

  <h1>{ws.title}</h1>
  <p class="page-desc">{ws.description}</p>

  <div class="worksheet-box">
    <div class="config-panel">
      <h3>Settings</h3>
      <div class="config-inputs">
        <div class="config-group">
          <label for="cfgProblems">Number of Problems</label>
          <input type="number" id="cfgProblems" value="8" min="5" max="15" />
        </div>
        <div class="config-group">
          <label for="cfgLevel">Difficulty Level</label>
          <select id="cfgLevel">
            <option value="easy">Easy</option>
            <option value="medium" selected>Medium</option>
            <option value="hard">Hard</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="worksheet-actions">
      <button class="ws-btn primary" id="btnGenerate">Generate New</button>
      <button class="ws-btn print" id="btnPrint">Print</button>
      <label class="toggle-label">
        <input type="checkbox" id="toggleAnswers" />
        Show Answers
      </label>
    </div>

    <div class="worksheet-content" id="worksheetContent">
      <div class="worksheet-header-print">
        <h2>Cause and Effect Practice</h2>
        <div class="name-date">
          <span>Name: ___________________</span>
          <span>Date: ___________________</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-grid reading-grid" id="problemGrid"></div>
      <div class="answer-key hidden" id="answerKey">
        <h3>Answer Key</h3>
        <div class="answer-grid" id="answerGrid"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <AdUnit slot="ws-mid" format="rectangle" />

  <article class="content-section">
    <h2>Understanding Cause and Effect</h2>
    <p>Cause and effect is a core reading comprehension skill that helps students understand why things happen in a text. A cause is the reason something occurs, and an effect is what happens as a result. Recognizing this relationship allows students to follow the logic of both fiction and nonfiction, make predictions, and understand how events in a story or real-world scenario are connected. This skill is tested on virtually every standardized reading assessment from elementary through high school.</p>
    <p>These worksheets present short passages followed by questions that ask students to identify either the cause or the effect described in the text. At the easy level, signal words like "because," "so," and "as a result" make the relationship explicit. At harder levels, the cause-and-effect connection may be implied, requiring students to read more carefully and think critically about what they have read.</p>

    <h2>Signal Words for Cause and Effect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cause signal words:</strong> because, since, due to, as a result of, the reason for, caused by, on account of</li>
      <li><strong>Effect signal words:</strong> so, therefore, as a result, consequently, thus, led to, for this reason</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Teaching students to spot these signal words is one of the most effective strategies for improving their ability to identify cause-and-effect relationships. However, students should also understand that many cause-and-effect relationships are stated without signal words, and they must infer the connection from context.</p>

    <h2>Tips for Teaching Cause and Effect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Start with everyday examples.</strong> Ask students: "What happens when you leave ice cream in the sun?" The cause is the heat; the effect is melting.</li>
      <li><strong>Use graphic organizers.</strong> A simple two-column chart labeled "Cause" and "Effect" helps students organize their thinking.</li>
      <li><strong>Look for chains.</strong> In many passages, one effect becomes the cause of another event, creating a chain reaction.</li>
      <li><strong>Practice with both fiction and nonfiction.</strong> Stories have character-driven causes and effects, while informational texts have factual ones.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Related Worksheets</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/worksheets/reading-main-idea-worksheets/">Main Idea Worksheets</a> - Identify the central idea of reading passages.</li>
      <li><a href="/worksheets/reading-inference-worksheets/">Making Inferences Worksheets</a> - Draw conclusions from text evidence.</li>
      <li><a href="/worksheets/reading-sequencing-worksheets/">Sequencing Worksheets</a> - Put events in the correct order.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <AdUnit slot="ws-bottom" format="horizontal" />
</BaseLayout>

<script is:inline>
  var selected = [];

  var passageBank = {
    easy: [
      { text: "It rained heavily all morning, so the soccer game was canceled.", question: "What was the effect of the heavy rain?", choices: ["A) The field was muddy", "B) The soccer game was canceled", "C) The players got wet", "D) It stopped raining"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Sarah forgot to water her plant for two weeks. When she finally checked on it, the leaves had turned brown and wilted.", question: "What caused the plant's leaves to wilt?", choices: ["A) Too much sunlight", "B) Sarah forgot to water it", "C) The pot was too small", "D) The soil was bad"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The boy stayed up very late watching TV. The next morning, he could barely keep his eyes open in class.", question: "Why was the boy tired in class?", choices: ["A) The class was boring", "B) He was sick", "C) He stayed up late watching TV", "D) He woke up too early"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Because the temperature dropped below freezing, the puddles on the sidewalk turned to ice.", question: "What caused the puddles to freeze?", choices: ["A) It snowed", "B) Someone poured water", "C) The temperature dropped below freezing", "D) The sun went down"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Mia practiced piano every day after school. By the end of the year, she could play several difficult songs perfectly.", question: "What was the effect of Mia practicing every day?", choices: ["A) She quit piano", "B) She could play difficult songs perfectly", "C) She got a new piano", "D) Her teacher was strict"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The alarm clock did not go off, so Jake was late for school.", question: "What caused Jake to be late?", choices: ["A) He missed the bus", "B) He forgot his backpack", "C) The alarm clock did not go off", "D) There was traffic"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The dog knocked over the glass of water. As a result, the homework on the table got soaked.", question: "What was the effect of the dog knocking over the glass?", choices: ["A) The dog got wet", "B) The homework got soaked", "C) The glass broke", "D) The table was ruined"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Lily ate too much candy at the party. Later that evening, she had a stomachache.", question: "What caused Lily's stomachache?", choices: ["A) She was nervous", "B) She ate too much candy", "C) She drank soda", "D) The party was loud"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Since there was no wind, the kite would not fly. Ben waited at the park, but the kite just lay on the ground.", question: "Why wouldn't the kite fly?", choices: ["A) The kite was broken", "B) Ben didn't run fast enough", "C) There was no wind", "D) The string was too short"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The baker added too much salt to the bread dough. When the bread came out of the oven, nobody wanted to eat it.", question: "What was the effect of adding too much salt?", choices: ["A) The bread didn't rise", "B) Nobody wanted to eat the bread", "C) The oven broke", "D) The bread burned"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Emma studied hard for her spelling test. She got every word correct and earned a perfect score.", question: "What was the effect of Emma studying hard?", choices: ["A) She missed school", "B) She got a perfect score", "C) The test was easy", "D) She forgot the words"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The strong winds blew the fence down during the storm. The next morning, the neighbor's dog got out through the gap.", question: "What caused the dog to get out?", choices: ["A) Someone left the gate open", "B) The dog dug under the fence", "C) The wind blew the fence down", "D) The neighbor let it out"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Tommy left his bicycle out in the rain for several months. Eventually, the chain and gears became covered in rust.", question: "Why did the bicycle rust?", choices: ["A) Tommy rode it too much", "B) It was left out in the rain for months", "C) The bicycle was old", "D) Someone broke it"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Because the store ran out of chocolate ice cream, Maria chose vanilla instead.", question: "What caused Maria to choose vanilla?", choices: ["A) She prefers vanilla", "B) Vanilla was on sale", "C) The store ran out of chocolate", "D) Her friend chose vanilla"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The teacher turned off the lights and closed the blinds. Then she started the movie on the screen for the class to watch.", question: "Why did the teacher turn off the lights?", choices: ["A) To save electricity", "B) So students could see the movie better", "C) The lights were broken", "D) It was time to go home"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Dad forgot to put gas in the car. On the way to school, the car stopped in the middle of the road.", question: "What caused the car to stop?", choices: ["A) There was a red light", "B) The tire was flat", "C) Dad forgot to put gas in the car", "D) There was traffic"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The cat knocked the fishbowl off the counter. The bowl shattered and water spilled all over the floor.", question: "What was the effect of the cat knocking over the fishbowl?", choices: ["A) The cat got wet", "B) The fish was happy", "C) The bowl shattered and water spilled", "D) Mom bought a new bowl"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Amy wore her new shoes without socks. By the end of the day, she had painful blisters on her feet.", question: "What caused Amy's blisters?", choices: ["A) The shoes were too small", "B) She walked too far", "C) She wore new shoes without socks", "D) Her feet were wet"], answer: "C" }
    ],
    medium: [
      { text: "After the city planted hundreds of new trees along Main Street, residents noticed that the area felt cooler during summer. The trees provided shade and released moisture into the air, lowering the temperature by several degrees.", question: "What was the effect of planting trees along Main Street?", choices: ["A) Traffic decreased on Main Street", "B) The area felt cooler in summer", "C) More birds came to the city", "D) Property values increased"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The factory upstream released chemicals into the river for years without anyone noticing. Eventually, fish populations declined sharply, and the water became unsafe for swimming or drinking.", question: "What caused the fish population to decline?", choices: ["A) Overfishing by local residents", "B) A natural drought lowered water levels", "C) The factory released chemicals into the river", "D) New predators entered the river"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "When the school added a free breakfast program, attendance rates improved significantly. Students who had previously skipped class because they were hungry now had a reason to arrive on time every morning.", question: "What was the effect of the free breakfast program?", choices: ["A) Students ate less at lunch", "B) Attendance rates improved", "C) The school hired more cooks", "D) Fewer students brought lunch from home"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The inventor Thomas Edison tested over a thousand different materials before finding one that worked as a light bulb filament. His persistence and willingness to learn from failure eventually led to one of the most important inventions in history.", question: "What caused Edison to succeed in inventing the light bulb?", choices: ["A) He was the smartest inventor", "B) He had unlimited funding", "C) His persistence and willingness to learn from failure", "D) Another inventor helped him"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "After volunteers cleaned up the local beach and installed recycling bins, sea turtle nesting increased for the first time in a decade. Fewer plastic bags and debris meant the turtles could safely dig nests in the sand.", question: "What caused sea turtle nesting to increase?", choices: ["A) Warmer ocean temperatures", "B) New laws protecting turtles", "C) The beach was cleaned up and recycling bins were installed", "D) More turtles migrated to the area"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The ancient city of Pompeii was buried under volcanic ash when Mount Vesuvius erupted in 79 AD. The thick layer of ash preserved buildings, artwork, and even food, giving modern archaeologists an incredibly detailed snapshot of Roman life.", question: "What was the effect of the volcanic eruption on Pompeii?", choices: ["A) The city was rebuilt immediately", "B) The city was buried and preserved under ash", "C) People evacuated safely", "D) The volcano became dormant"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "When smartphones became affordable, people began reading fewer printed newspapers. Many local newspapers could not make enough money from advertising and subscriptions, so they were forced to close.", question: "What caused many local newspapers to close?", choices: ["A) People stopped reading altogether", "B) Paper became too expensive", "C) Smartphones reduced demand for printed newspapers", "D) Journalists went on strike"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The town built a new bike path connecting neighborhoods to the downtown area. As a result, more residents began cycling to work and local shops instead of driving, reducing traffic congestion noticeably.", question: "What was the effect of building the bike path?", choices: ["A) More people moved to the town", "B) Gas prices went down", "C) More residents cycled and traffic congestion decreased", "D) Parking lots were expanded"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Because coral reefs provide shelter for thousands of fish species, the destruction of reefs from pollution and rising temperatures has led to significant declines in fish populations. Fishing communities that depend on reef fish for their livelihood are now struggling economically.", question: "What caused fishing communities to struggle?", choices: ["A) Overfishing emptied the ocean", "B) Fish migrated to colder waters", "C) Reef destruction reduced fish populations they depend on", "D) New fishing regulations were imposed"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Maria's family switched from processed snacks to fruits and vegetables. Within a few months, Maria had more energy during the day, slept better at night, and improved her grades in school.", question: "What was the effect of switching to healthier food?", choices: ["A) Maria lost weight", "B) Maria had more energy, better sleep, and improved grades", "C) Maria started exercising more", "D) Maria's family spent less on groceries"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The heavy snowfall blocked all the roads leading out of the mountain town. Delivery trucks could not get through, and the grocery stores began running low on food and supplies.", question: "What caused stores to run low on supplies?", choices: ["A) A workers' strike stopped deliveries", "B) Heavy snowfall blocked roads so trucks could not deliver", "C) The stores forgot to order more", "D) Demand suddenly increased"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "After the library extended its hours to include evenings and weekends, the number of visitors nearly doubled. Parents who worked during the day could now bring their children after dinner.", question: "What was the effect of extending library hours?", choices: ["A) The library hired fewer staff", "B) Book borrowing decreased", "C) The number of visitors nearly doubled", "D) The library moved to a new building"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Deforestation in the highlands removed the tree roots that held the soil in place. When the rainy season arrived, massive mudslides swept down the bare hillsides and damaged homes in the valley below.", question: "What caused the mudslides?", choices: ["A) An earthquake loosened the soil", "B) Deforestation removed tree roots that stabilized the soil", "C) The rain was unusually heavy that year", "D) Construction work weakened the hillside"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The school replaced old fluorescent lights with energy-efficient LED bulbs throughout the building. Over the course of the year, the electricity bill dropped by nearly thirty percent, saving thousands of dollars.", question: "What was the effect of switching to LED bulbs?", choices: ["A) Classrooms were brighter", "B) Students performed better on tests", "C) The electricity bill dropped by nearly thirty percent", "D) The school replaced all its equipment"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "A drought lasting several years dried up the watering holes that elephants relied on during the dry season. Herds were forced to travel much farther to find water, bringing them into conflict with farmers whose crops they trampled.", question: "What caused elephants to come into conflict with farmers?", choices: ["A) Poachers drove them from their habitat", "B) The elephant population grew too large", "C) Drought dried up watering holes, forcing herds to travel into farmland", "D) Farmers moved closer to elephant territory"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "When the city banned single-use plastic bags, shoppers initially complained about the inconvenience. However, within a year, litter in parks and waterways decreased by over forty percent, and most residents supported the policy.", question: "What was the effect of banning plastic bags?", choices: ["A) Stores lost money", "B) Litter in parks and waterways decreased significantly", "C) People stopped shopping", "D) More plastic was produced"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The invention of the telegraph in the 1830s allowed messages to travel across long distances in minutes rather than weeks by horseback or ship. This revolutionized business, journalism, and military communication almost overnight.", question: "What was the effect of the telegraph's invention?", choices: ["A) Horses became obsolete", "B) Long-distance communication became nearly instant, transforming many fields", "C) Newspapers stopped printing", "D) Ships were no longer used"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "After the zoo introduced an enrichment program that gave animals puzzles, hiding spots, and foraging activities, visitors noticed that the animals were more active and playful. Veterinarians also reported improvements in the animals' physical health.", question: "What caused the animals to become more active?", choices: ["A) The zoo got new animals", "B) The enrichment program provided stimulating activities", "C) Visitors fed the animals more food", "D) The weather improved"], answer: "B" }
    ],
    hard: [
      { text: "The introduction of invasive cane toads to Australia in 1935 was intended to control beetle populations damaging sugarcane crops. However, the toads had no natural predators and their poisonous skin killed native animals that tried to eat them. Cane toad populations exploded, and native species like quolls and freshwater crocodiles suffered significant declines.", question: "What was the unintended effect of introducing cane toads?", choices: ["A) Sugarcane production increased dramatically", "B) Beetles adapted and became resistant", "C) Native predators declined because the toads were poisonous and had no natural enemies", "D) The toads eventually died out"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "When the city raised parking fees downtown and simultaneously expanded bus routes, public transit ridership increased by twenty-five percent within six months. However, some small business owners complained that fewer customers were driving to their shops.", question: "What caused the increase in public transit ridership?", choices: ["A) Gas prices rose sharply", "B) The city gave free bus passes to all residents", "C) Higher parking fees and expanded bus routes made transit more attractive", "D) A new train line opened downtown"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The overuse of antibiotics in both medicine and livestock farming has accelerated the evolution of antibiotic-resistant bacteria, often called superbugs. Infections that were once easily treatable now require stronger and more expensive drugs, and in some cases, no effective treatment exists.", question: "What caused the rise of antibiotic-resistant bacteria?", choices: ["A) Bacteria naturally become resistant over time", "B) Overuse of antibiotics in medicine and farming accelerated resistance", "C) New types of bacteria were discovered", "D) Hospitals became less clean"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "After Iceland made its geothermal energy freely available for heating homes, the country virtually eliminated its dependence on imported fossil fuels for residential heating. Air quality improved dramatically, and heating costs for families dropped to near zero.", question: "What were the effects of using geothermal energy for heating?", choices: ["A) Iceland exported excess energy to Europe", "B) Fossil fuel dependence ended, air quality improved, and heating costs dropped", "C) Homes needed new heating systems", "D) Geothermal plants caused earthquakes"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The collapse of the cod fishery off the coast of Newfoundland in 1992, caused by decades of overfishing, led to the loss of nearly 40,000 jobs and devastated coastal communities that had relied on fishing for generations. The Canadian government imposed a moratorium on cod fishing, but populations have still not fully recovered more than thirty years later.", question: "What caused the collapse of the cod fishery?", choices: ["A) Climate change warmed the ocean", "B) A disease killed the cod population", "C) Decades of overfishing depleted the cod stocks", "D) Pollution poisoned the fishing grounds"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Research has shown that children who are read to regularly from an early age develop larger vocabularies and stronger reading skills than children who are not. This early exposure to language patterns and storytelling builds neural pathways that support literacy, critical thinking, and academic success throughout school and beyond.", question: "What is the effect of reading to children regularly?", choices: ["A) Children learn to read earlier than their peers", "B) Children develop larger vocabularies, stronger reading skills, and better academic outcomes", "C) Parents bond more closely with their children", "D) Children prefer reading to playing"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "When wolves were reintroduced to Yellowstone National Park in 1995, a cascade of ecological changes followed. The wolves reduced elk populations, which allowed overgrazed vegetation along rivers to recover. Stronger riverbank vegetation reduced erosion, and the rivers themselves began to change course less frequently.", question: "What was the far-reaching effect of reintroducing wolves?", choices: ["A) Elk populations increased and moved to new areas", "B) Vegetation recovered, erosion decreased, and river patterns stabilized", "C) Wolves became the dominant predator and eliminated all elk", "D) Tourists stopped visiting the park"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The widespread adoption of social media has been linked to rising rates of anxiety and depression among teenagers. Studies suggest that constant comparison with curated online profiles, cyberbullying, and sleep disruption from late-night screen use all contribute to declining mental health in this age group.", question: "What are the effects of social media on teenagers' mental health?", choices: ["A) Teenagers have become more socially connected and happier", "B) Rising anxiety and depression due to comparison, bullying, and sleep disruption", "C) Teenagers spend less time on homework", "D) Social media has no measurable effect on mental health"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The construction of the Aswan High Dam in Egypt controlled the annual flooding of the Nile River, providing reliable irrigation and hydroelectric power. However, the dam also trapped nutrient-rich silt that had fertilized farmland downstream for thousands of years, forcing farmers to rely on expensive chemical fertilizers.", question: "What was an unintended consequence of the Aswan High Dam?", choices: ["A) The Nile stopped flowing entirely", "B) Downstream farmland lost natural fertilization from trapped silt", "C) Flooding became worse downstream", "D) Egypt no longer needed to import food"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "When a massive asteroid struck Earth approximately 66 million years ago, it triggered tsunamis, earthquakes, and a cloud of dust that blocked sunlight for months. Temperatures plummeted, photosynthesis slowed, and food chains collapsed. This chain of events led to the extinction of approximately 75 percent of all species, including the non-avian dinosaurs.", question: "What was the ultimate effect of the asteroid impact?", choices: ["A) Earth's atmosphere was permanently altered", "B) Dinosaurs evolved into birds", "C) Approximately 75 percent of species went extinct due to cascading environmental effects", "D) The oceans evaporated completely"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The green revolution of the 1960s introduced high-yield crop varieties and modern farming techniques to developing countries, dramatically increasing food production. While millions were saved from famine, the heavy reliance on chemical pesticides and fertilizers depleted soil nutrients and contaminated groundwater in many regions.", question: "What were the mixed effects of the green revolution?", choices: ["A) Food production increased but soil and water quality suffered", "B) Farmers became wealthy but stopped growing traditional crops", "C) Crop varieties decreased and famines worsened", "D) Only wealthy countries benefited from the new techniques"], answer: "A" },
      { text: "After the Chernobyl nuclear disaster in 1986, a 30-kilometer exclusion zone was established around the reactor. With humans absent for decades, wildlife has unexpectedly flourished in the zone. Wolves, wild horses, and rare bird species now roam areas that were once farmland and towns, demonstrating nature's remarkable ability to recover when human activity ceases.", question: "What caused wildlife to flourish in the Chernobyl exclusion zone?", choices: ["A) Radiation caused beneficial mutations in animals", "B) The absence of human activity allowed nature to recover", "C) Scientists deliberately introduced wildlife", "D) The radiation levels dropped to zero quickly"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The rapid melting of Arctic sea ice due to climate change has opened new shipping routes through the Northwest Passage, reducing travel time between Europe and Asia. However, the same melting threatens polar bear habitats, raises global sea levels, and disrupts weather patterns far from the Arctic by weakening the jet stream.", question: "What are the contrasting effects of Arctic ice melting?", choices: ["A) Shipping benefits but wildlife, sea levels, and weather patterns are harmed", "B) New land is being discovered under the ice", "C) The Arctic is becoming warmer and more habitable for humans", "D) Polar bears are adapting well to the changes"], answer: "A" },
      { text: "The invention of air conditioning transformed life in hot climates by making indoor spaces comfortable year-round. Cities in the American South and Middle East experienced population booms as people could now live and work comfortably despite extreme heat. However, the energy consumed by air conditioning contributes significantly to greenhouse gas emissions, creating a cycle where cooling the indoors warms the planet.", question: "What is the ironic consequence of air conditioning?", choices: ["A) People moved away from hot climates", "B) Cooling indoor spaces contributes to the global warming that makes cooling necessary", "C) Air conditioning became too expensive to use", "D) Hot climates became cooler overall"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The policy of mandatory seat belt use, introduced in many countries during the 1970s and 1980s, met initial resistance from drivers who viewed it as government overreach. Over time, however, seat belt usage rates climbed above 90 percent in most developed countries, and traffic fatalities dropped by an estimated 45 percent. The policy is now widely regarded as one of the most successful public health measures in modern history.", question: "What was the long-term effect of mandatory seat belt laws?", choices: ["A) People drove more recklessly because they felt safer", "B) Traffic fatalities dropped significantly and the policy gained widespread support", "C) Car manufacturers opposed the requirement", "D) Seat belt use remained below 50 percent"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Intensive monoculture farming, where a single crop is planted over vast areas year after year, maximizes short-term yields but degrades soil health over time. Without crop rotation, the soil loses essential nutrients, becomes more susceptible to erosion, and requires increasing amounts of chemical fertilizers to maintain productivity. This creates a cycle of diminishing returns that threatens long-term food security.", question: "What is the long-term effect of monoculture farming?", choices: ["A) Crop yields increase indefinitely", "B) Soil health degrades, creating a cycle of diminishing productivity", "C) Farmers save money by growing one crop", "D) Soil naturally regenerates between planting seasons"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The development of GPS technology, originally designed for military navigation, has had far-reaching effects on civilian life. It enabled ride-sharing apps, precision agriculture, emergency response coordination, and even fitness tracking. This is a notable example of how technology created for one purpose can transform entirely unrelated industries and everyday activities.", question: "What is the broader effect described in this passage?", choices: ["A) Military technology always benefits civilians", "B) GPS, originally military, transformed many civilian industries and daily activities", "C) Ride-sharing apps replaced taxis", "D) Precision agriculture feeds more people"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "When streaming services like Netflix and Spotify became popular, they disrupted traditional media industries. Music sales and movie theater attendance declined as consumers preferred the convenience and lower cost of streaming. However, the shift also created new opportunities for independent artists and filmmakers who could now reach global audiences without needing a major studio or record label.", question: "What were the dual effects of streaming services?", choices: ["A) Traditional media declined but independent creators gained new opportunities", "B) Everyone stopped going to movie theaters entirely", "C) Record labels and studios became more powerful", "D) Streaming services replaced all other forms of entertainment"], answer: "A" }
    ]
  };

  function shuffle(arr) {
    for (var i = arr.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
      var j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
      var temp = arr[i]; arr[i] = arr[j]; arr[j] = temp;
    }
    return arr;
  }

  function generateProblems() {
    var count = parseInt(document.getElementById('cfgProblems').value, 10);
    var level = document.getElementById('cfgLevel').value;

    if (isNaN(count) || count < 5) count = 5;
    if (count > 15) count = 15;

    var pool = passageBank[level].slice();
    shuffle(pool);
    selected = pool.slice(0, Math.min(count, pool.length));

    renderProblems();
    renderAnswerKey();
    updateAnswerVisibility();
  }

  function renderProblems() {
    var grid = document.getElementById('problemGrid');
    var showAnswers = document.getElementById('toggleAnswers').checked;
    var html = '';

    for (var i = 0; i < selected.length; i++) {
      var p = selected[i];
      html += '<div class="reading-passage">';
      html += '<div class="problem-number">' + (i + 1) + ')</div>';
      html += '<div class="passage-text">' + p.text + '</div>';
      html += '<div class="passage-question"><strong>' + p.question + '</strong></div>';
      html += '<div class="passage-choices">';
      for (var j = 0; j < p.choices.length; j++) {
        var isCorrect = showAnswers && p.choices[j].charAt(0) === p.answer;
        html += '<div class="choice' + (isCorrect ? ' correct' : '') + '">' + p.choices[j] + '</div>';
      }
      html += '</div>';
      html += '</div>';
    }

    grid.innerHTML = html;
  }

  function renderAnswerKey() {
    var answerGrid = document.getElementById('answerGrid');
    var html = '';
    for (var i = 0; i < selected.length; i++) {
      html += '<div class="answer-item">';
      html += '<span class="q">' + (i + 1) + '.</span>';
      html += '<span class="a">' + selected[i].answer + '</span>';
      html += '</div>';
    }
    answerGrid.innerHTML = html;
  }

  function updateAnswerVisibility() {
    var showAnswers = document.getElementById('toggleAnswers').checked;
    var answerKey = document.getElementById('answerKey');
    if (showAnswers) { answerKey.classList.remove('hidden'); }
    else { answerKey.classList.add('hidden'); }
    renderProblems();
  }

  document.getElementById('btnGenerate').addEventListener('click', generateProblems);
  document.getElementById('btnPrint').addEventListener('click', function () { window.print(); });
  document.getElementById('toggleAnswers').addEventListener('change', updateAnswerVisibility);
  generateProblems();
</script>
